        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 4:04PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 403 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Hobbs State Park, moving northeast at 35 mph. Another strong
thunderstorm was located near Beaver Lake, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Rockhouse...                      War Eagle...
Beaver Lake...                    Larue...
Pleasant Ridge...                 Gateway...
Urbanette...                      Hobbs State Park...
Berryville...                     Beaver...
Grandview...                      Best...
Clifty...                         Oak Hill...
Busch...                          Lookout...
Eureka Springs...                 Garfield...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
